# Taking Over Error Handling

You can define your own function to handle errors using `set_error_handler()`. This function will be called whenever an error occurs (except fatal errors).

```php
function myErrorHandler($errno, $errstr, $errfile, $errline) {
    echo "Error [$errno]: $errstr in $errfile on line $errline";
    // You can log, display custom page, etc.
    return true; // indicate error handled
}

set_error_handler('myErrorHandler');
```

To restore the previous handler, use `restore_error_handler()`.

```php
<?php
function customError($errno, $errstr) {
    echo "<b>Custom Error:</b> [$errno] $errstr<br>";
    error_log("Error: $errstr"); // log to server error log
}

set_error_handler('customError');

echo $undefinedVar; // triggers custom handler
echo "Script continues...";
?>
```
